It is a very different matter to say that a pickup group would be added to the rotation if it managed to kill VS.  Who would you say is in the rotation?  A pickup group?  40 players assembled by Darmu using a message board and in-game tells?  Darmu himself?<br>
<br>
Sooner or later, someone is going to take down VS with a pickup group.  It will be interesting to see how things work out. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uparum.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Parum</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 281<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/29/01 8:52:51 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: how many people are interested in a VS pick up?</span><hr size=1> Tormentia - The reason people got mad at DG was because they were *already* in the rotation and were not up to kill him, yet did anyways.  MC just KSed him last week and no one was mad... at least I saw no one mad. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ubarridor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Barridor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 50<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/29/01 11:22:50 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: how many people are interested in a VS pick up?</span><hr size=1> I think if a pickup raid can get their shit together well enough to take VS down.. all power to them. I wish ye the best of luck.. Ill be very impressed to see that.. I dont think any of the guilds in the rotation will be pissed about it.. as long as you dont pull over a guidl thats buffing for it.. ahem.. nuff sed. <p><img src=http://members.home.net/barridor/Barridorsig.gif>
